{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "This autonomy allows contributors to gravitate toward innovation types that align with their motivations and expertise (Miric and Jeppesen 2023; Piezunka and Dahlander 2019) enabling diverse innovation pathways than in directed settings.",
    "The introduction of LLMs into voluntary collaborative environments creates a particularly revealing natural experiment because these tools may differentially impact the cognitive and coordination demands of capability versus iterative innovation (Hoffmann et al. 2024).",
    "Observing how self-selecting contributors adjust their innovation focus in response to LLM availability will help understand the underlying mechanisms through which these technologies reshape the innovation processes in the knowledge domain.",
    "Extant literature (Brynjolfsson et al. 2025; Noy and Zhang 2023) has not investigated LLMs' impact on voluntary collaborative environments where contributions intertwine and build upon each other.",
    "Furthermore, the voluntary, unguided nature of open-source development creates unique dynamics that may amplify or transform LLMs' effects compared to organizational contexts (von Krogh et al. 2012)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "This autonomy allows contributors to gravitate toward innovation types that align with their motivations and expertise (Miric and Jeppesen 2023; Piezunka and Dahlander 2019) enabling diverse innovation pathways than in directed settings.",
